    <!-- ── Features ── -->
    <section class="section" id="features">
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="section-lead">
          <span class="eyebrow">What you get</span>
          <h2>The missing layer around coding agents.</h2>
          <p>
            Chat is only one part of supervising an agent. Sidemesh keeps the rest of
            the workstation close too: approvals, files, git context, terminals,
            ports, and previews.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="feature-grid">

          <article class="feature-card">
            <div class="feature-icon" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 18 18" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
                <rect x="1" y="2" width="16" height="12" rx="2"/>
                <path d="M6 16h6M9 14v2"/>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <h3>Session control</h3>
            <p>Running sessions, pending approvals, transcript events, and host status — reachable across all paired machines from one place.</p>
          </article>

          <article class="feature-card">
            <div class="feature-icon" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 18 18" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
                <path d="M9 2l2 5h5l-4 3 1.5 5L9 12l-4.5 3L6 10 2 7h5z"/>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <h3>Approvals, surfaced</h3>
            <p>Blocked sessions don't stay blocked. Pending decisions get their own space instead of disappearing into transcript history.</p>
          </article>

          <article class="feature-card">
            <div class="feature-icon" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 18 18" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
                <path d="M10 2H4a1 1 0 00-1 1v12a1 1 0 001 1h10a1 1 0 001-1V7l-5-5z"/>
                <path d="M10 2v5h5M6 10h6M6 13h4"/>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <h3>Workspace inspection</h3>
            <p>Browse files, render markdown, review git context, and inspect generated assets before approving the agent's next step.</p>
          </article>

          <article class="feature-card">
            <div class="feature-icon" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 18 18" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
                <rect x="1" y="2" width="16" height="14" rx="2"/>
                <path d="M5 7l3 3-3 3M10 13h4"/>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <h3>Terminal access</h3>
            <p>Attach to a host shell when chat is not enough. Deliberately gated — kept behind the private network where host access is intentional.</p>
          </article>

          <article class="feature-card">
            <div class="feature-icon" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 18 18" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
                <circle cx="4.5" cy="9" r="2.5"/>
                <circle cx="13.5" cy="9" r="2.5"/>
                <path d="M7 9h4"/>
                <path d="M10.5 7.5l2.5 1.5-2.5 1.5"/>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <h3>Port forwarding</h3>
            <p>Reach dev servers running on the remote machine from your phone or desktop — without exposing the host to the public internet.</p>
          </article>

          <article class="feature-card">
            <div class="feature-icon" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 18 18" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
                <rect x="1" y="3" width="16" height="13" rx="2"/>
                <path d="M1 7h16M5 5h.01M7.5 5h.01M10 5h.01"/>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <h3>Browser preview</h3>
            <p>Stream a live browser running on the host when visual state matters. No tunnel, no staging server, no extra tooling needed.</p>
          </article>

        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

